         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });

               <div onClick="selectSearchType('u');" id="searchtype_u" class="searchtype_option">User</div>
               <div onClick="selectSearchType('p');" id="searchtype_p" class="searchtype_option">Boards</div>
               <div onClick="selectSearchType('s');" id="searchtype_s" class="searchtype_option">List</div>

         </div>
      </div>
   </form>
  </div>
  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>


</div>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    margin-top: 1em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
   }
         </style> 
      <div id="report_ads" style="    ">

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <p><i>Which ad on the page is the source of the problem?  (if there are multiple, just pick the worst one)</i></p>

         <div id="report_ads_list">



         </div>

         <label for="report_ad_description">Please describe the ad and situation in as much detail as possible (including any brand names, product names, domain names you might have seen)</label>

         <textarea id="report_ad_unit_html"></textarea>

         <button id="report_ad_submit" onClick="reportAdSubmit()">Submit</button>

      </div>

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };

               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

<table><tr><td style="width:100%;text-align:center;"><address>&copy; 2000 - 2016 Sonemic, Inc. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a id="report_ad_link" style="cursor:pointer;" onClick="reportAdOpen();">report ads</a><script>


      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

            };

               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

            googletag.__display = googletag.display;

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>


</div>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    margin-top: 1em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
   }
         </style> 
      <div id="report_ads" style="    ">

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <p><i>Which ad on the page is the source of the problem?  (if there are multiple, just pick the worst one)</i></p>

         <div id="report_ads_list">



         </div>

         <label for="report_ad_description">Please describe the ad and situation in as much detail as possible (including any brand names, product names, domain names you might have seen)</label>

   <script> function areAdsBlocked() { return ($('#ad_1').length == 0) } 
   function politeAdRequest() {
      var xx = '<div class=abpmessage>RYM relies on advertising income to support the site.  Please consider adding an exception to adblock for rateyourmusic.com, or <a href="/subscribe/">becoming a subscriber</a>.</div>' 
      $('#content').prepend(xx)
   }

   </script>
 
      <script>
                  if(areAdsBlocked()) {   
                     politeAdRequest()

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };

               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;

    background: #f8f8f8;

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

         googletag.cmd.push(function () {
            googletag.pubads().setTargeting('pagetype', ['chart'])
               .setTargeting('pb_timeout','d950')
               .setTargeting('case','')
               .setTargeting('logged_in','false')

            slotRendered = false;


            pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = false;

            googletag.__display = googletag.display;

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });
      </script></head>

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }

        var googletag = googletag || {};
        googletag.cmd = googletag.cmd || [];

        (function() {
          var gads = document.createElement('script');
          gads.async = true;
          gads.type = 'text/javascript';
          var useSSL = 'https:' == document.location.protocol;
          gads.src = (useSSL ? 'https:' : 'http:') +

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

         googletag.cmd.push(function () {

               .setTargeting('pb_timeout','d950')

               .setTargeting('logged_in','false')

            slotRendered = false;


            pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = false;

            googletag.__display = googletag.display;

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });

         ▶
      </div>

      onFocus="$('#search_options').show()" onBlur="$('#search_options').hide();" onKeyDown="cycleSearchType(event);">
         <span id="searchtype_selected">Artists</span> ▾

            <div class="search_option_header">Music</div>
               <div onClick="selectSearchType('a');" id="searchtype_a" class="searchtype_option current">Artists</div>

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>


</div>

<table><tr><td style="width:100%;text-align:center;"><address>&copy; 2000 - 2016 Sonemic, Inc. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a id="report_ad_link" style="cursor:pointer;" onClick="reportAdOpen();">report ads</a><script>


      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) {

                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };

               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>


</div>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    margin-top: 1em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
   }

      <div id="report_ads" style="    ">

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <p><i>Which ad on the page is the source of the problem?  (if there are multiple, just pick the worst one)</i></p>

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

<table><tr><td style="width:100%;text-align:center;"><address>&copy; 2000 - 2016 Sonemic, Inc. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a id="report_ad_link" style="cursor:pointer;" onClick="reportAdOpen();">report ads</a><script>


      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    margin-top: 1em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
   }

      <div id="report_ads" style="    ">

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <p><i>Which ad on the page is the source of the problem?  (if there are multiple, just pick the worst one)</i></p>

                   return bidCpm * 0.84779; // 0.85 * 0.987
                 }
               },
               districtm: {
                 bidCpmAdjustment : function(bidCpm){
                   return bidCpm * 0.89532; // 0.9 * 0.9948
                 }
               },
               springserve: {
                 bidCpmAdjustment : function(bidCpm){
                   return bidCpm * 0.9787; // 1.0 * 0.9787
                 }
               },
               pulsepoint: {
                 bidCpmAdjustment : function(bidCpm){
                   return bidCpm * 1.0062; // 1.0 * 1.0062
                 }                  
               },
               sekindo: {
                 bidCpmAdjustment : function(bidCpm){
                   return bidCpm * 1.0078; // 1.0 * 1.0078
                 }
               },
               aol: {
                 bidCpmAdjustment : function(bidCpm){
                   return bidCpm * 0.87312; // 1.0 * 0.87312
                 }
               }

             };
           </script>

      <script type='text/javascript'>
        var googletag = googletag || {};
        googletag.cmd = googletag.cmd || [];

        googletag.cmd.push(function() {
            googletag.pubads().disableInitialLoad();
        });



        (function() {
          var gads = document.createElement('script');
          gads.async = true;
          gads.type = 'text/javascript';
          var useSSL = 'https:' == document.location.protocol;
          gads.src = (useSSL ? 'https:' : 'http:') +
            '//www.googletagservices.com/tag/js/gpt.js';
          var node = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];
          node.parentNode.insertBefore(gads, node);
        })();
      </script>
   
         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

            googletag.__display = googletag.display;

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });
      </script></head>

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }

        (function() {

          gads.async = true;
          gads.type = 'text/javascript';
          var useSSL = 'https:' == document.location.protocol;
          gads.src = (useSSL ? 'https:' : 'http:') +

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

            slotRendered = false;


            pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = false;

            googletag.__display = googletag.display;

            googletag.display = function(unit) {

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };


            googletag.pubads().addEventListener('slotRenderEnded', function(event) {
               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });

      </div>

      onFocus="$('#search_options').show()" onBlur="$('#search_options').hide();" onKeyDown="cycleSearchType(event);">
         <span id="searchtype_selected">Artists</span> ▾

               <div onClick="selectSearchType('a');" id="searchtype_a" class="searchtype_option current">Artists</div>

  <script>
      function cycleSearchType(event) {

         var searchTypes = new Array('a', 'l', 'y', 'b', 'j', 'r', 'v', 'g', 'F', 'A', 'u', 'p', 's');
         var len = searchTypes.length;
         var currentVal = $('#searchtype').val();
         var currentIndex = searchTypes.indexOf(currentVal);
         var nextIndex = currentIndex+1;
         var prevIndex = currentIndex-1;
         if ( nextIndex == len ) {
            nextIndex = 0;
         }
         if ( prevIndex < 0 ) {
            prevIndex = len-1;
         }

         var nextType = searchTypes[nextIndex];
         var prevType = searchTypes[prevIndex];


         switch (event.keyCode) {
            case 40: 
               selectSearchType(nextType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 38:
               selectSearchType(prevType);
               event.preventDefault();
            break;

            case 13:
               $('#mainsearch')[0].submit();
               event.preventDefault();
            break;
            default: 
               
            break;
         }

        
         return false;

      }
      function selectSearchType(type) {
         $('#searchtype').val(type);
         $('#searchtype_selected').text($('#searchtype_' + type).text());
         $('#search_options').hide();
      }
      selectSearchType('a')

  </script>


</div>

      function reportAdOpen() {
         $('#report_ads').toggle();
         reportAdPopulateList();
      }

      function reportAdPopulateList() {


         var ret = '';

         for ( i in rymads ) {


            var ad = rymads[i];

            ret += '<label for="report_ad_' + i + '"><input type="radio" id="report_ad_' + i + '" onClick="reportAdSelect(\'' + i + '\');" name="report_ad_unit" value="' + i + '"> ' + ad.description + '</label>';

         }

         $('#report_ads_list').html(ret);
      }

      function reportAdSubmit() {

         var ad_type = $('input[name=report_ad_type]:checked').val();
         var ad_unit = $('input[name=report_ad_unit]:checked').val();

         var description = $('#report_ad_description').val();
         var ad_json = $('#report_ad_json').val();
         var ad_unit_html = $('#report_ad_unit_html').val();

         var url = window.location.pathname;

         rym.request.post('AdsReport', { ad_type:ad_type, ad_unit:ad_unit, description:description, ad_json:ad_json, ad_unit_html:ad_unit_html, url:url } , null, 'script');

      }

      function _reportAdCallback(message) {
         $('#report_ads').html(message);
      }

      function reportAdSelect(id) {
         $('#report_ad_unit_html').val( $('#' + id).html());
      }

      </script><style>#report_ads label { display:block;margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;} 
   #report_ad_submit {  padding:0.5em; border:1px solid #ddd; background:#f0f0f0; font-size:1.1em; }
   #report_ad_description { width:100%; height:5em; border:1px solid #eee; background:#fff; padding:0.5em; }
   #report_ad_json, #report_ad_unit_html { display:none; }
   #report_ads {
      display:none;
      text-align: left;
    max-width: 40em;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2em;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    margin-top: 1em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
   }
         </style> 
      <div id="report_ads" style="    ">

         <p>Advertisers are not allowed to run annoying ads on RYM.   You can use this form to report problematic or annoying ads.  </p>

          <p>If you are still on the page where the annoying ad was (or still is) displayed, then proceed to fill out this form. </p>

          <p>If the ads navigated you to another page, then use the back button to navigate back to the exact page where the problem started and submit from there.</p>

         <p><i>What is problematic about the ad?</i></p>

            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="sound"> The ad is playing sound without having interacted with it.</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="cover"> The ad partially covered site content</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="total_cover"> The ad completely covered site content (like a popup, but without opening a new window)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="new_window"> The ad opened a new tab or window</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="store_redirect"> The ad redirected my mobile browser to the app store or another app</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="report_ad_type" value="other"> Other (please clarify in comments)</label>

         <p><i>Which ad on the page is the source of the problem?  (if there are multiple, just pick the worst one)</i></p>

         <div id="report_ads_list">

      var xx = '<div class=abpmessage>RYM relies on advertising income to support the site.  Please consider adding an exception to adblock for rateyourmusic.com, or <a href="/subscribe/">becoming a subscriber</a>.</div>' 
      $('#content').prepend(xx)
   }

         <script>

         var pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = false;
         pbjs.pubAdsRetries = 0;
         pbjs.displayCallRetries = 0;

         function initAdserver() {
           if (pbjs.initAdserverSet) return;

           //we don't want to call DFP before it is ready
           if( (!googletag.pubadsReady || !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits) && pbjs.retries <= PREBID_MAX_RETRIES) {
             if ( !googletag.pubadsReady ) {
                pbjs.pubAdsRetries++;
             }
             if ( !pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits ) {
                pbjs.displayCallRetries++;               
             }

             setTimeout(initAdserver, 100);
             pbjs.retries++;
             return;
           }

           console.log ( pbjs.retries + ' retries needed: ' + pbjs.pubAdsRetries + ' waiting for pubAds and ' + pbjs.displayCallRetries + ' waiting for display()')


           googletag.cmd.push(function () {
             pbjs.que.push(function () {
               pbjs.setTargetingForGPTAsync();
             });


             pubAdsReadyOnRefresh = googletag.pubadsReady;
             googletag.pubads().refresh();

             setTimeout(function() {
               if ( !slotRendered && !areAdsBlocked() ) {
                  rym.request.post('MarkFailedDfpRender', {par:pubAdsReadyOnRefresh}, null, 'script');
               }
              }, 5000);

           });
           pbjs.initAdserverSet = true;
         }


        pbjs.que.push(function() {
           pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
           pbjs.requestBids({
             bidsBackHandler: function(bidResponses) {
                initAdserver();
              },
             timeout : PREBID_TIMEOUT
           });
         }); 

       </script>

               var retvalue = googletag.__display(unit);

               console.log ('displaying ' + unit);
               rymads[unit].loaded = true;

               var allLoaded = true;

               for ( var i in rymads ) { 

                  if ( !rymads[i].loaded ) {
                     allLoaded = false;
                     break;
                  }

               }

               if ( allLoaded ) {
                  pbjs.displayCalledOnAllUnits = true;
               }

               return retvalue;

            };

               slotRendered = true;
            });

            googletag.enableServices();
      
        });
